<h2 id="neercs">neercs</h2>
<p>
neercs is a work-in-progress libcaca project.
</p>
<p>
Like GNU screen, it allows you to detach a session from a terminal, but provides unique features:
</p>
<ul><li>Grabbing a process that you forgot to start inside neercs
</li><li>Great screensaver
</li><li>3D rotating cube to switch between full screen terms
</li><li>Real time thumbnails of your shells
</li><li>Special effects when closing a window
</li><li>Various window layouts...
</li></ul><p>
neercs was written by Sam Hocevar, Jean-Yves Lamoureux and Pascal Terjan. It is free software, and can be used, modified and distributed under the terms of the <a class="ext-link" href="http://sam.zoy.org/wtfpl/"><span class="icon">Do What The Fuck You Want To Public License</span></a>.
</p>
<h2 id="Development">Development</h2>
<p>
Development happens in a centralised Subversion repository:
</p>
<ul><li><a class="ext-link" href="svn://svn.zoy.org/caca/neercs/trunk"><span class="icon">svn://svn.zoy.org/caca/neercs/trunk</span></a>
</li><li>associated <a href="http://caca.zoy.org/browser/neercs/trunk">web interface</a>
</li></ul><p>
There is also a Git repository that mirrors the central one:
</p>
<ul><li>using the Git protocol: <a class="ext-link" href="git://git.zoy.org/neercs.git"><span class="icon">git://git.zoy.org/neercs.git</span></a>
</li><li>using HTTP: <a href="http://caca.zoy.org/git/neercs.git">http://caca.zoy.org/git/neercs.git</a>
</li></ul><p>
If you want to discuss neercs or report bugs, you can subscribe to the libcaca mailing-list or join #libcaca on irc.freenode.net.
</p>
